| Q                   | A
| --------------------| ---------------
| PHPUnit version     | 11.3.0
| PHP version         | 8.3.6
| Installation Method | Composer

#### Summary

As the result of https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/5415, the classes with method named `method` are deprecated and will not be supported once https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/issues/5416 lands. The #5415 asks `when do you call a method ``method``?`. Laravel does this 10+ years, see https://github.com/laravel/framework/commit/a7056b8d740e19d3d26716daad8af222e46a357a

#### Current behavior

```
Class Illuminate\Http\Request has a method named "method". Doubling classes that have a method named "method" is deprecated. Support for this will be removed in PHPUnit 12.
```

#### How to reproduce

```php
<?php declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Tests\Unit;

use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class TestRequest extends \PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase
{
    public function test1(): void
    {
        $this->createMock(Request::class);
    }
}
```

#### Expected behavior

The testing framework should not have an opinion on how to name the methods.
